Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE and
NEEDS_ATTENTION as success, and DELETING as
terminating; FAILED is terminal and DELETED is
only a delete-confirmation target.
Create, update, and delete responses expose
work-request headers but do not return a Fleet
body. The runtime resumes through
GetWorkRequest, recovers the affected Fleet OCID
from work-request resources, and then rereads
GetFleet before settling.
Pre-create reuse only runs when
spec.compartmentId and spec.displayName are
present and keeps exact compartmentId plus
displayName matching bounded to ACTIVE,
CREATING, UPDATING, or NEEDS_ATTENTION
summaries.
Only displayName, description, inventoryLog,
operationLog, isAdvancedFeaturesEnabled,
freeformTags, and definedTags reconcile in
place; operationLog updates only when both log
identifiers are supplied, compartmentId remains
replacement-only, and ChangeFleetCompartment
stays out of scope for the published runtime.
inventoryLog remains a required published spec
field because CreateFleet requires it from the
first published contract.
Required status projection keeps approximate
inventory counters, inventoryLog, operationLog,
export-setting state, and systemTags on the
published kind, and the runtime has no secret
side effects.
end note
